specimen RA346
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,905,1182]" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">
Our recent study of the material collected in 1981 by Danish colleagues from Chile revealed one specimen (slide no. RA346, ZMUC) which externally was almost identical to 
<emphasis box="[849,988,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">
G. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Diškus &amp; Solis" authorityYear="2017" box="[880,988,941,966]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Glaucolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flagellata">flagellata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
but in the male genitalia had no a large compact cluster of spines near phallotrema and, compared with 
<emphasis box="[880,1020,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">
G. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Diškus &amp; Solis" authorityYear="2017" box="[912,1020,977,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Glaucolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flagellata">flagellata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, its genitalia capsule is smaller: 300 µm long, 195 µm wide. We recognize it as a new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braun" authorityYear="1917" box="[830,965,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Glaucolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[830,965,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Glaucolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we left it undescribed because of the severely broken adult in a plastic tube and rather poor genitalia slide. This specimen RA346 belongs to the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">
G. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Diškus &amp; Solis" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,259,1085,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Glaucolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flagellata">flagellata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
